4th, I think most folks in China

00:28:06.070 --> 00:28:08.380
do recognize what that means.

00:28:08.380 --> 00:28:12.100
And so it's trying to find
within that cat and mouse game,

00:28:12.100 --> 00:28:16.374
trying to find this to walk the
line of being evasive, but not

00:28:16.374 --> 00:28:17.790
so evasive that
you don't actually

00:28:17.790 --> 00:28:18.960
connect with internet users.

00:28:18.960 --> 00:28:22.130
So in terms of actual
age, Weibo is primarily,

00:28:22.130 --> 00:28:26.400
like most social media,
a youth-driven media-- so

00:28:26.400 --> 00:28:27.710
folks, college kids.

00:28:27.710 --> 00:28:31.890
But it's also really
been this powerful tool

00:28:31.890 --> 00:28:35.010
for not just youth
and their frivolous

00:28:35.010 --> 00:28:38.370
posting pictures of what
they did last night,

00:28:38.370 --> 00:28:41.560
but also for activists
and journalists.

00:28:41.560 --> 00:28:45.882
So you'll find a lot of those
folks online on Weibo, as well.

00:28:45.882 --> 00:28:51.284
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE] did
